Cheers!

productname: Tecnifibre Carboflex 130 Basaltex Squash Racket
Tecnifibre Suprem Calibur 135 Squash Racket
Cosco Lst 125 Squash Racket
Prince Airstick 130 Squash Racket

SP:
I bought this racket being a Ramy Ashour fan boy. Looking to change my game and be more dynamic in my shots like Ramy, the air-stick was very maneuverable and easy to control.

Initially the racket was a disappointment with the factory strings. I changed to a 1.18 gauge string and it become a dream to play afterward giving me a lot of control and feel. I've recommended this racket to 5 of my other friends in my club and now we're all synchronized. A very popular racket since it suites any level of play.

Still looking for the Black and Gold liverly though since that's the one Ramy uses, heard it's not in stock in India anymore.
Great for someone who's used to prince rackets.  Extremely whippy and powerful

For players with defending, counter-hitting style, this could be the super-fast champion of the net. Although I wouldn’t state this can be a girls racket, I do see a large amount of girls loving this racket because especially in mixed doubles.

This against all is just a price-point that will be fairly large and could even not be on -placing for many. In certain areas this can be a very hard racket to charge. About the hand, I’m not too sure this can attract people as well as in certain, which kind of player picks up this and drops in love. The actual bad here's that I wonder whether according to solid feel and reliability point for large power shots, there's been a decrease in the effectiveness particularly within the look for weight-reduction.

SP: I used to use normal overgrips for Tennis. But the problem with the normal "non tacky" grips is that they lose the grippy surface fast and you are forced to change the overgrips often. But the story is different with these "tacky" grips. As the name suggests, these grips have a tacky, gummy surface. They last long and provide excellent grip. You don't have to use lot of force to hold your tennis racket in position during the play. In My opinion, this is the best tennis grip ever.

Fitbit ONE Wireless Activity and Sleep Tracker

SP:
I've been trying this product for about two weeks now and I'm loving it. The interface is simple and clean and not flashy so you don't get distracted by it when you're working. It syncs with the phone just fine, as long as your phone has bluetooth options. It keeps track of every movement you make and gives easy-to-follow analysis on your laptop/mobile/tab.

One of the good things is that when it's with you 24x7, it comes with silent alarms options so you don't disturb those around you. One thing that is important is that if you want it to analyse your sleep quality then you need to wear it on your wrist. I generally tuck it with my belt during the day so taking it off and attaching it to the wrist strap every night is a task. I've just started using the wrist strap during the day too and after some initial adjustment, it sits on the wrist perfectly, leaves no marks but I'm worried about tan lines. 

As far as performance is concerned, this device is simple and easy to use and keeps you on your toes. Getting a daily analysis of your progress is encouraging and I've been eating better and taking stairs now that I know it goes on the log. :)

I can finally figure out why I can't sleep properly!! This is a great and fun device and it syncs easily with phones and an app called FitnessBuddy. With the Fitbit One transmitting the data to my phone, I can check any minute how many calories I'm burning. It's great for analyzing sleep too, one of my biggest problems. I had fun competing against my friends and it really motivated me to get active. It's an awesome device and once you go to FitnessBuddy you can join a whole community of people who are using the same device and hoping to get fit.

The best part is that even when you're driving, it counts the movements, especially if you have it strapped on the wrist. NOTHING is left out. So you know EXACTLY where you stand. The comparison graphs on the phone explain improvement, the condition of your body and all very accurately. This is a great device and definitely worth the price. So far, my only concern is dust when I'm travelling or walking on the road but I've avoided that by tucking it inside the cuffs of my shirt. 

Great product and really fast delivery!

I'm not big on fitness so I had to think long and hard before blowing 8k on a device. To be honest, I hadn't even heard of activity trackers before. I read up the product description here and did bit of a google search and decided to take the leap. After all, if a device promises so much it must deliver something.

Firstly, the shipping and delivery were super. I mean, I got it far sooner than I had anticipated and once I put  this on, I realized it delivers on EVERY COUNT. Seriously, keeping the price in mind and the fact that I've been using without any glitches for more than ten days now, I can say this is the best thing in fitness to happen.

The cool thing about the gadget that it pushes you to change your lifestyle gradually. It makes you take small steps towards fitness and that's great for people like me. I don't want to have to worry about heading to the gym after work. If I know that climbing the stairs to my office and flat burns X amount of calories, I'll just do that instead. The awesome bit is that Fitbit tells me what I can do, small alterations here and there to make a change in my fitness status. So not only does it track stuff but also recommends stuff.

I don't find it weird to wear around my wrist while sleeping because I've always worn a watch and it doesn't rub against the skin or leave any marks. I've started wearing it on the wrist all day because mostly,  I'm scared of it falling off from my belt, though it does latch on firmly. The design is simple and efficient, I've been wearing it to work without causing any dress code issues so that's cool. I have the black version and it's pretty sleek and hasn't gotten any scratches on or something.

It'd be epic if my friends could buy this because it comes with amazing options and fun fitness stuff to compete with your friends. 

The USB bits had me terrified but they actually connect and charge the device just fine. The silent alarm is a little mellow and didn't really affect me but honestly I didn't buy the product for the alarm so that's okay. Syncs easily, takes about a minute to set up.

I think it's a must for any fitness freak or even if you are trying to get back in shape (like me;)).

I was shocked when i first saw how few steps i took for the day. Daily/hourly feedback is a great motivator to take the daily steps and then more. Highly recommended.

SP:
This product is just out of this world! Amazing stuff from Fitbit, it is truly one of those moments when you think Tech is going rule over all of us. 

I feel everything about my workout is calculted and precise to the decimal. No more wondering if I did indeed burn enough calories to attain my deficit needs to loose weight. 

The best thing is that it looks at your data and makes recommendations to ur diet and lifestyle. It's greatly made me a healthier person in general. Plus it's uber cool to wear as well!
Amazing Product. The best thing to push yourself. A must have for any fitness enthusiast. Good service. Keep it up!

This device is pretty great, that is you understand limitations from other products LYS sells. It clearly is way better than the Jawbone UP which is honestly like a big pain in the ass to use.

I won't say I'm a big fitness freak, more of a gadget freak and was really curious into looking into wearable tech especially after CES 2013. 

This is my first Fitbit product and activity tracker, so please keep that in mind. 

First off, from a build quality point of view, the product's presentation is stellar and looks damn sexy and hot when I wear it to the gym or just casually out meeting friends ( coming from a girl). Get a lot of jealous stares. Certainly an eye catches, the black version realy goes well and stands out. It's comfortable when you have it on, but it's difficult to push the clasp together to hold it on. It doesn't feel like it wants to come off when you do have it on though. Also, I spend a lot of time on my desk in office typing stuff out on my keyboard and it's very comfortable to type with it on. (this surprised me). 

Luckily, it comes with two sets of bands (large and small), a USB charging dongle, a USB syncing nub, and the activity tracker itself. 

Setting it up to your body and workouts is a breeze, just go to the URL listed on the paper, download the software, and sync your tracker with the USB syncing device. 

It asks you to "double tap" the device to sync, feels like every tech might go that ( google glass-esque). 

I own an iPhone 5s and the syncing is almost instantaneous. It appears that the syncing frequency between devices is at 15 minute intervals. It takes a minute to manually sync devices, but I don't feel like that's necessary unless you're in desperate need of motivation/feedback. 

I read somewhere that these wrist devices sometimes mistake arm movement for steps, but that is not the case here. It's really a bummer that it doesn't have a built in altimeter like the Ultra and I imagine that the 2nd generation Flex will have that built in. As for the activity lights, I thought they would be always on, but instead you have to double tap the device for them to show up. That's not a bad thing, but if you realy wanted to feel right out of a RoboCop movie this would have been really cool.

The sleep tracker/silent alarm function was a huge selling point for me with this device. I'm a little disappointed that the sleep tracking/alarm isn't as robust as the Jawbone Up's.

This excellent product. Certain things I like most that it gives notification when battery is getting low or drain out. Sync is good. I am not sure but during car driving also it catches the movement and add steps count which I do not like since it is not realistic count. You can easily cheat by moving hand rapidly staying single place which increases step count. it depends upon whether we want to cheat or not. Overall this product is really good and i am motivated for walk daily.

productname: Jawbone Up 24 Bluetooth Enabled Wristband Large Black Color

SP: Best wearable model till date with a fantastic battery life! With the coolest app companion, provides better personal and insightful advice. Kudos to Jawbone! Highly recommended.

Amazing design with a supremely crafted interface! Has definitely overpowered the downfalls of the original Up. Superb battery. For me, its an absolute showstopper among all the activity trackers. Wish the company could have compromised with the fat price tag.

Holds me accountable to me goals to the best extent. Much better and advanced than the Up, Up24 is fantastically Apptastic! Thanks to the wireless syncing. Just hope Jawbone plans to introduce an intuitive display next for readability.

its an excellent product, mostly due to its app, which is very simple and very informative, most of the time i found it to be pretty ok as far as accuracy is concerned, i still feel lack of small display is a con, but it can be ignored as the design is good and is comfortable to wear.

one point which i would like to mention is that i got a rash on my right hand after a certain period of use, i m not sure whether anyone else encountered the same problem, it was not a very serious issue, but yes, minor irritation still persists after prolong period of use. 
overall i would say its an excellent product with minor cons.

SP:
I run long distance and complete atleast two half marathons a year alongwith all the training runs which are usually above 5k. I'm also flat-footed only in my left foot (very weird,I know) and earlier used to used Nike Lunarlites albeit with a special arch support after being sidelined with runners knee for 3 months.

I bought these shoes right before I went for a Euro-Trip where I knew I would have to walk a lot on cobbled streets. These shoes were a life-saver! Trust me, everytime I wear these shoes they feel like slipping on pillows on your feet. They're amazing shoes and are perfect for mild-overpronators like me. 

It's fairly lightweight for the level of cushioning and I just don't use these shoes for running anymore, it fits perfectly for my HIIT and Cross-Fit training as well as going for long walks.

I am a marathoner and clock b/w 40 - 50 Km a week, have used Nike ( Lunarlon /  Pegasus  / Vomero / Free Run) and Asics ( Noosa /  Gel K 19) and these better most in terms of weight / comfort /  sweat /  cushion and of course price! SP: The gear is a perfect alibi for Trekking, Cycling, Backpacking & especially for Music Festivals. The main compartment designed is perfect for storing valuables like Passports, Mobile Phones, Wallet, Keys, Hand towels, etc. Frequent usable items such as Cash, Credit Cards, Debit Cards & Tokens could be stored on either of the side zipped pockets. A great gear to get freedom from Items in the shirt and pant pockets. The quality & material maintains the originality of the product. Last but not the least, the Camelbak Octane XCT 3L comes with a sleek compartment to pack 3 liters of power packed juice to keep you hydrated all throughout the day. Not recommended for alcohol or revitalizing drinks such as gatorade because it may leave a sticky texture and a bad odour. Totally worth the money spent for. LYS offers the lowest price in the Indian market as of now. If your in 2 minds to purchase this accessory, I would personally recommend to purchase it with no regrets. The after sale service of LYS is exceptionally great & responsive.
